claim.claim-text:
6. A picture display device comprising: 
a cathode ray tube (CRT) for displaying a video signal (VID); 
deflection means (Ll, Lf) for deflecting an electron beam (201) in the cathode ray tube (CRT); 
an electron gun (200) in the cathode ray tube (CRT) for generating the electron beam (201), comprising a DAF section (220) for dynamically adapting a focusing and an astigmatism of the electron beam (201) in dependence upon the deflection of the electron beam (201); 
a deflection circuit (D), coupled to the deflection means (Ll, Lf), for generating a line-frequency deflection current (Idl) and a field-frequency deflection current (Idf), synchronized with the video signal (VID), and 
a dynamic focusing circuit (100) as claimed in any one of claims 1 to 5, supplying the line-frequency focusing voltage (Vl1) to the DAF section (220).
